{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":794,"text":"Hi. So I'd like to talk a little bit about the people"},{"time":3210,"text":"who make the things we use every day:"},{"time":5739,"text":"our shoes, our handbags, our computers and cell phones."},{"time":9499,"text":"Now, this is a conversation that often calls up a lot of guilt."},{"time":13945,"text":"Imagine the teenage farm girl who makes less than"},{"time":17536,"text":"a dollar an hour stitching your running shoes,"},{"time":20392,"text":"or the young Chinese man who jumps off a rooftop"},{"time":23090,"text":"after working overtime assembling your iPad."},{"time":27130,"text":"We, the beneficiaries of globalization, seem to exploit"},{"time":30738,"text":"these victims with every purchase we make,"},{"time":33441,"text":"and the injustice"},{"time":35074,"text":"feels embedded in the products themselves."},{"time":38163,"text":"After all, what's wrong with a world in which a worker"},{"time":40723,"text":"on an iPhone assembly line can't even afford to buy one?"},{"time":44499,"text":"It's taken for granted that Chinese factories are oppressive,"},{"time":47149,"text":"and that it's our desire for cheap goods"},{"time":49880,"text":"that makes them so."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52241,"text":"So, this simple narrative equating Western demand"},{"time":56056,"text":"and Chinese suffering is appealing,"},{"time":58868,"text":"especially at a time when many of us already feel guilty"},{"time":61503,"text":"about our impact on the world,"},{"time":64081,"text":"but it's also inaccurate and disrespectful."},{"time":67864,"text":"We must be peculiarly self-obsessed to imagine that we"},{"time":70848,"text":"have the power to drive tens of millions of people"},{"time":74016,"text":"on the other side of the world to migrate and suffer"},{"time":76728,"text":"in such terrible ways."},{"time":79523,"text":"In fact, China makes goods for markets all over the world,"},{"time":82341,"text":"including its own, thanks to a combination of factors:"},{"time":85929,"text":"its low costs, its large and educated workforce,"},{"time":89335,"text":"and a flexible manufacturing system"},{"time":91801,"text":"that responds quickly to market demands."},{"time":94952,"text":"By focusing so much on ourselves and our gadgets,"},{"time":98001,"text":"we have rendered the individuals on the other end"},{"time":100464,"text":"into invisibility, as tiny and interchangeable"},{"time":103824,"text":"as the parts of a mobile phone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106879,"text":"Chinese workers are not forced into factories"},{"time":109544,"text":"because of our insatiable desire for iPods."},{"time":112023,"text":"They choose to leave their homes in order to earn money,"},{"time":115095,"text":"to learn new skills, and to see the world."},{"time":119048,"text":"In the ongoing debate about globalization, what's"},{"time":121441,"text":"been missing is the voices of the workers themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124872,"text":"Here are a few."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127177,"text":"Bao Yongxiu: \"My mother tells me to come home"},{"time":130926,"text":"and get married, but if I marry now, before I have fully"},{"time":134650,"text":"developed myself, I can only marry an ordinary worker,"},{"time":138735,"text":"so I'm not in a rush.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":141238,"text":"Chen Ying: \"When I went home for the new year,"},{"time":144280,"text":"everyone said I had changed. They asked me,"},{"time":147536,"text":"what did you do that you have changed so much?"},{"time":150633,"text":"I told them that I studied and worked hard. If you tell them"},{"time":153911,"text":"more, they won't understand anyway.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":157279,"text":"Wu Chunming: \"Even if I make a lot of money,"},{"time":160664,"text":"it won't satisfy me."},{"time":162815,"text":"Just to make money is not enough meaning in life.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":167184,"text":"Xiao Jin: \"Now, after I get off work, I study English,"},{"time":171896,"text":"because in the future, our customers won't"},{"time":173685,"text":"be only Chinese, so we must learn more languages.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":177547,"text":"All of these speakers, by the way, are young women,"},{"time":180318,"text":"18 or 19 years old."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183400,"text":"So I spent two years getting to know assembly line workers"},{"time":186342,"text":"like these in the south China factory city called Dongguan."},{"time":190271,"text":"Certain subjects came up over and over:"},{"time":192791,"text":"how much money they made,"},{"time":194695,"text":"what kind of husband they hoped to marry,"},{"time":197074,"text":"whether they should jump to another factory"},{"time":199199,"text":"or stay where they were."},{"time":201399,"text":"Other subjects came up almost never, including"},{"time":203592,"text":"living conditions that to me looked close to prison life:"},{"time":207039,"text":"10 or 15 workers in one room,"},{"time":209322,"text":"50 people sharing a single bathroom,"},{"time":212681,"text":"days and nights ruled by the factory clock."},{"time":216015,"text":"Everyone they knew lived in similar circumstances,"},{"time":219503,"text":"and it was still better than the dormitories and homes"},{"time":222264,"text":"of rural China."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224832,"text":"The workers rarely spoke about the products they made,"},{"time":227558,"text":"and they often had great difficulty explaining"},{"time":229902,"text":"what exactly they did."},{"time":232344,"text":"When I asked Lu Qingmin,"},{"time":234055,"text":"the young woman I got to know best,"},{"time":236157,"text":"what exactly she did on the factory floor,"},{"time":238624,"text":"she said something to me in Chinese that sounded like"},{"time":241029,"text":"\"qiu xi.\""},{"time":242806,"text":"Only much later did I realize that she had been saying"},{"time":245775,"text":"\"QC,\" or quality control."},{"time":248999,"text":"She couldn't even tell me what she did on the factory floor."},{"time":252862,"text":"All she could do was parrot a garbled abbreviation"},{"time":255319,"text":"in a language she didn't even understand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259313,"text":"Karl Marx saw this as the tragedy of capitalism,"},{"time":262935,"text":"the alienation of the worker from the product of his labor."},{"time":266978,"text":"Unlike, say, a traditional maker of shoes or cabinets,"},{"time":270602,"text":"the worker in an industrial factory has no control,"},{"time":273849,"text":"no pleasure, and no true satisfaction or understanding"},{"time":277106,"text":"in her own work."},{"time":279297,"text":"But like so many theories that Marx arrived at"},{"time":281713,"text":"sitting in the reading room of the British Museum,"},{"time":284532,"text":"he got this one wrong."},{"time":287358,"text":"Just because a person spends her time"},{"time":289657,"text":"making a piece of something does not mean"},{"time":292425,"text":"that she becomes that, a piece of something."},{"time":294977,"text":"What she does with the money she earns,"},{"time":298080,"text":"what she learns in that place, and how it changes her,"},{"time":301585,"text":"these are the things that matter."},{"time":304346,"text":"What a factory makes is never the point, and"},{"time":306646,"text":"the workers could not care less who buys their products."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310730,"text":"Journalistic coverage of Chinese factories,"},{"time":313218,"text":"on the other hand, plays up this relationship"},{"time":315330,"text":"between the workers and the products they make."},{"time":318159,"text":"Many articles calculate: How long would it take"},{"time":321248,"text":"for this worker to work in order to earn enough money"},{"time":324092,"text":"to buy what he's making?"},{"time":326552,"text":"For example, an entry-level-line assembly line worker"},{"time":329040,"text":"in China in an iPhone plant would have to shell out"},{"time":332312,"text":"two and a half months' wages for an iPhone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":335857,"text":"But how meaningful is this calculation, really?"},{"time":339194,"text":"For example, I recently wrote an article"},{"time":341184,"text":"in The New Yorker magazine,"},{"time":342162,"text":"but I can't afford to buy an ad in it."},{"time":345401,"text":"But, who cares? I don't want an ad in The New Yorker,"},{"time":347457,"text":"and most of these workers don't really want iPhones."},{"time":350322,"text":"Their calculations are different."},{"time":353082,"text":"How long should I stay in this factory?"},{"time":354896,"text":"How much money can I save?"},{"time":357359,"text":"How much will it take to buy an apartment or a car,"},{"time":359929,"text":"to get married, or to put my child through school?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":364519,"text":"The workers I got to know had a curiously abstract"},{"time":367210,"text":"relationship with the product of their labor."},{"time":370968,"text":"About a year after I met Lu Qingmin, or Min,"},{"time":374110,"text":"she invited me home to her family village"},{"time":376144,"text":"for the Chinese New Year."},{"time":378367,"text":"On the train home, she gave me a present:"},{"time":380753,"text":"a Coach brand change purse with brown leather trim."},{"time":385144,"text":"I thanked her, assuming it was fake,"},{"time":386817,"text":"like almost everything else for sale in Dongguan."},{"time":390294,"text":"After we got home, Min gave her mother another present:"},{"time":394103,"text":"a pink Dooney &amp; Bourke handbag,"},{"time":396288,"text":"and a few nights later, her sister was showing off"},{"time":398711,"text":"a maroon LeSportsac shoulder bag."},{"time":402215,"text":"Slowly it was dawning on me that these handbags"},{"time":406015,"text":"were made by their factory,"},{"time":408032,"text":"and every single one of them was authentic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411198,"text":"Min's sister said to her parents,"},{"time":413663,"text":"\"In America, this bag sells for 320 dollars.\""},{"time":417025,"text":"Her parents, who are both farmers, looked on, speechless."},{"time":420064,"text":"\"And that's not all -- Coach is coming out with a new line,"},{"time":422623,"text":"2191,\" she said. \"One bag will sell for 6,000.\""},{"time":427424,"text":"She paused and said, \"I don't know if that's 6,000 yuan or"},{"time":431671,"text":"6,000 American dollars, but anyway, it's 6,000.\" (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":437318,"text":"Min's sister's boyfriend, who had traveled home with her"},{"time":439913,"text":"for the new year, said,"},{"time":442030,"text":"\"It doesn't look like it's worth that much.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":444863,"text":"Min's sister turned to him and said, \"Some people actually"},{"time":447688,"text":"understand these things. You don't understand shit.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":451232,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":455887,"text":"In Min's world, the Coach bags had a curious currency."},{"time":459927,"text":"They weren't exactly worthless, but they were nothing"},{"time":462247,"text":"close to the actual value, because almost no one they knew"},{"time":464957,"text":"wanted to buy one, or knew how much it was worth."},{"time":468887,"text":"Once, when Min's older sister's friend got married,"},{"time":472242,"text":"she brought a handbag along as a wedding present."},{"time":475070,"text":"Another time, after Min had already left"},{"time":477238,"text":"the handbag factory, her younger sister came to visit,"},{"time":480380,"text":"bringing two Coach Signature handbags as gifts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484491,"text":"I looked in the zippered pocket of one,"},{"time":486566,"text":"and I found a printed card in English, which read,"},{"time":490805,"text":"\"An American classic."},{"time":494063,"text":"In 1941, the burnished patina"},{"time":496573,"text":"of an all-American baseball glove"},{"time":498935,"text":"inspired the founder of Coach to create"},{"time":501135,"text":"a new collection of handbags from the same"},{"time":503544,"text":"luxuriously soft gloved-hand leather."},{"time":506753,"text":"Six skilled leatherworkers crafted 12 Signature handbags"},{"time":510928,"text":"with perfect proportions and a timeless flair."},{"time":515064,"text":"They were fresh, functional, and women everywhere"},{"time":517344,"text":"adored them. A new American classic was born.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":522680,"text":"I wonder what Karl Marx would have made of Min"},{"time":525006,"text":"and her sisters."},{"time":526914,"text":"Their relationship with the product of their labor"},{"time":529521,"text":"was more complicated, surprising and funny"},{"time":531816,"text":"than he could have imagined."},{"time":534074,"text":"And yet, his view of the world persists, and our tendency"},{"time":536897,"text":"to see the workers as faceless masses,"},{"time":539506,"text":"to imagine that we can know what they're really thinking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":543380,"text":"The first time I met Min, she had just turned 18"},{"time":546781,"text":"and quit her first job on the assembly line"},{"time":549436,"text":"of an electronics factory."},{"time":551751,"text":"Over the next two years, I watched as she switched jobs"},{"time":554397,"text":"five times, eventually landing a lucrative post"},{"time":557473,"text":"in the purchasing department of a hardware factory."},{"time":561047,"text":"Later, she married a fellow migrant worker,"},{"time":563572,"text":"moved with him to his village,"},{"time":565714,"text":"gave birth to two daughters,"},{"time":567917,"text":"and saved enough money to buy a secondhand Buick"},{"time":570105,"text":"for herself and an apartment for her parents."},{"time":574511,"text":"She recently returned to Dongguan on her own"},{"time":577644,"text":"to take a job in a factory that makes construction cranes,"},{"time":581260,"text":"temporarily leaving her husband and children"},{"time":583460,"text":"back in the village."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585443,"text":"In a recent email to me, she explained,"},{"time":588024,"text":"\"A person should have some ambition while she is young"},{"time":592070,"text":"so that in old age she can look back on her life"},{"time":594732,"text":"and feel that it was not lived to no purpose.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":599515,"text":"Across China, there are 150 million workers like her,"},{"time":603911,"text":"one third of them women, who have left their villages"},{"time":606664,"text":"to work in the factories, the hotels, the restaurants"},{"time":610207,"text":"and the construction sites of the big cities."},{"time":612812,"text":"Together, they make up the largest migration in history,"},{"time":616556,"text":"and it is globalization, this chain that begins"},{"time":619556,"text":"in a Chinese farming village"},{"time":622075,"text":"and ends with iPhones in our pockets and Nikes on our feet"},{"time":625852,"text":"and Coach handbags on our arms"},{"time":628276,"text":"that has changed the way these millions of people"},{"time":630565,"text":"work and marry and live and think."},{"time":635478,"text":"Very few of them would want to go back"},{"time":637427,"text":"to the way things used to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639984,"text":"When I first went to Dongguan, I worried that"},{"time":643164,"text":"it would be depressing to spend so much time with workers."},{"time":647539,"text":"I also worried that nothing would ever happen to them,"},{"time":650310,"text":"or that they would have nothing to say to me."},{"time":652939,"text":"Instead, I found young women who were smart and funny"},{"time":655589,"text":"and brave and generous."},{"time":658436,"text":"By opening up their lives to me,"},{"time":660767,"text":"they taught me so much about factories"},{"time":662973,"text":"and about China and about how to live in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":669486,"text":"This is the Coach purse that Min gave me"},{"time":672198,"text":"on the train home to visit her family."},{"time":674608,"text":"I keep it with me to remind me of the ties that tie me"},{"time":677251,"text":"to the young women I wrote about,"},{"time":679975,"text":"ties that are not economic but personal in nature,"},{"time":684245,"text":"measured not in money but in memories."},{"time":687812,"text":"This purse is also a reminder that the things that you imagine,"},{"time":691231,"text":"sitting in your office or in the library,"},{"time":694773,"text":"are not how you find them when you actually go out"},{"time":697176,"text":"into the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":698683,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":700671,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":707343,"text":"Chris Anderson: Thank you, Leslie, that was an insight"},{"time":709412,"text":"that a lot of us haven't had before."},{"time":712009,"text":"But I'm curious. If you had a minute, say,"},{"time":715496,"text":"with Apple's head of manufacturing,"},{"time":719217,"text":"what would you say?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":721577,"text":"Leslie Chang: One minute?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":722705,"text":"CA: One minute. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":724218,"text":"LC: You know, what really impressed me about the workers"},{"time":726144,"text":"is how much they're self-motivated, self-driven,"},{"time":729370,"text":"resourceful, and the thing that struck me,"},{"time":731987,"text":"what they want most is education, to learn,"},{"time":734952,"text":"because most of them come from very poor backgrounds."},{"time":736499,"text":"They usually left school when they were in 7th or 8th grade."},{"time":739443,"text":"Their parents are often illiterate,"},{"time":741682,"text":"and then they come to the city, and they, on their own,"},{"time":744322,"text":"at night, during the weekends, they'll take a computer class,"},{"time":746447,"text":"they'll take an English class, and learn"},{"time":748715,"text":"really, really rudimentary things, you know,"},{"time":750839,"text":"like how to type a document in Word,"},{"time":752578,"text":"or how to say really simple things in English."},{"time":755242,"text":"So, if you really want to help these workers,"},{"time":757370,"text":"start these small, very focused, very pragmatic classes"},{"time":760593,"text":"in these schools, and what's going to happen is,"},{"time":763722,"text":"all your workers are going to move on,"},{"time":765141,"text":"but hopefully they'll move on into higher jobs within Apple,"},{"time":768548,"text":"and you can help their social mobility"},{"time":771489,"text":"and their self-improvement."},{"time":772486,"text":"When you talk to workers, that's what they want."},{"time":774264,"text":"They do not say, \"I want better hot water in the showers."},{"time":776938,"text":"I want a nicer room. I want a TV set.\""},{"time":778923,"text":"I mean, it would be nice to have those things,"},{"time":780546,"text":"but that's not why they're in the city,"},{"time":781704,"text":"and that's not what they care about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":783793,"text":"CA: Was there a sense from them of a narrative that"},{"time":787343,"text":"things were kind of tough and bad, or was there a narrative"},{"time":790755,"text":"of some kind of level of growth, that things over time"},{"time":793768,"text":"were getting better?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":795391,"text":"LC: Oh definitely, definitely. I mean, you know,"},{"time":797298,"text":"it was interesting, because I spent basically two years"},{"time":799664,"text":"hanging out in this city, Dongguan,"},{"time":801658,"text":"and over that time, you could see immense change"},{"time":803769,"text":"in every person's life: upward, downward, sideways,"},{"time":806564,"text":"but generally upward."},{"time":808385,"text":"If you spend enough time, it's upward, and I met people"},{"time":810172,"text":"who had moved to the city 10 years ago, and who are now"},{"time":812467,"text":"basically urban middle class people,"},{"time":814574,"text":"so the trajectory is definitely upward."},{"time":816595,"text":"It's just hard to see when you're suddenly"},{"time":818530,"text":"sucked into the city. It looks like everyone's poor and"},{"time":820651,"text":"desperate, but that's not really how it is."},{"time":822389,"text":"Certainly, the factory conditions are really tough,"},{"time":824543,"text":"and it's nothing you or I would want to do,"},{"time":826860,"text":"but from their perspective, where they're coming from"},{"time":830005,"text":"is much worse, and where they're going"},{"time":832002,"text":"is hopefully much better, and I just wanted to give"},{"time":834010,"text":"that context of what's going on in their minds,"},{"time":836371,"text":"not what necessarily is going on in yours."}]},{"cues":[{"time":838734,"text":"CA: Thanks so much for your talk."},{"time":840230,"text":"Thank you very much. (Applause)"}]}]}